<br>
Mages need some cool class-level AAs, that make people go &quot;oooo, ahhh!&quot;<br>
<br>
What if mages had an AA to summon a 2nd pet.<br>
<br>
There are may ways this could be kept balanced: (no, not all of these, but . . .)<br>
1&gt; Reuse timers.<br>
<br>
2&gt; 2nd pet is a suicide pet (attacks target, dies when it has no hostile targets)<br>
<br>
3&gt; Pet's HPs are in the mage's manabar.  Run oom, pet dies.  Damage to pet is taken off mage's manabar.  /pet get lost has no effect on the mage's manabar.<br>
<br>
4&gt; Pet strength could be limited (Ie, 2nd pet is a L 44 pet-summon).<br>
<br>
5&gt; Pet commands could be syncronized.<br>
<br>
6&gt; Summoning a 2nd pet could take the mage's entire manabar (with the pet strength somehow being purportional to the manabar).<br>
<br>
7&gt; 2nd Pet HPs could be linked to the mage's HPs (like 3, but your life is at stake).<br>
<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd love to see the 2nd pet as:<br>
Linked to mage's manabar + and + HP bar. (1 point of damage to pet does 1 HP and 1 mana damage to mage).<br>
<br>
Can zone with you like BST pet.<br>
<br>
Short reuse timer (unsummon and resummon at will)<br>
<br>
Going invis just causes pet to poof, doesn't kill the mage/drain all the mage's mana.<br>
<br>
Only way to kill pet is to have the master go OOM/die.<br>
<br>
There could be a seperate class-AA for each type of pet, but only 1 of them works at once.  You could rapidly switch between them, however.<br>
